\cf0 This kind of world often occurs {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AfterTheEnd"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 After the End}}. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WretchedHive"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Wretched Hive}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CityNoir"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 City Noir}} are city-sized versions of the Crapsack World. A {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Dystopia"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Dystopia}} is a speculative Crapsack World ruled by repressive forces modeled after real-life politics. A {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeenageWasteland"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Teenage Wasteland}} is a Crapsack World run by kids. If the Crapsack World\'92s continued misery is caused by supernatural forces, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkFantasy"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Dark Fantasy}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HellOnEarth"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Hell on Earth}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CosmicHorrorStory"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Cosmic Horror Story}}.\
If a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SugarBowl"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Sugar Bowl}} (usually the antithesis of this trope) turns out to be one of these under the surface, then you have yourself a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrapsaccharineWorld"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Crapsaccharine World}}. If the people who live in the Crapsack World don\'92t realise or pretend it isn\'92t a horrible place to be in, it is a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FalseUtopia"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 False Utopia}}. A {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainWorld"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Villain World}} or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathWorld"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Death World}} is likely to be this, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadFuture"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Bad Future}} is a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubTrope"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Sub-Trope}}. Someone who just thinks the world they inhabit is this is a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCynic"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Cynic}} or a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrawNihilist"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Straw Nihilist}} (or a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GrumpyBear"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Grumpy Bear}}, if he lives in a pretty nice world).\
For worlds that are almost literal sacks of crap see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDungAges"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 The Dung Ages}}. See {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouWouldNotWantToLiveInDex"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 You Would Not Want to Live in Dex}} for other crapsack environments. On a less negative note, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorldOfBadass"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 World of Badass}} will also be likely to have elements of the Crapsack World, to give justification on why kicking ass is very important to survival. Compare {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorldOfJerkass"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 World of Jerkass}}, a world which is only unpleasant because all of the characters are horrible people.\
This trope is also known as World Half Empty, for the expression of pessimism being a state of seeing a glass with half the amount of water in it as being \'93half empty\'94. Also, a half-empty glass means it can only be emptied, and can\'92t be refilled. It represents {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 hopelessness}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FromBadToWorse"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 and inevitable doom}}, fitting this trope perfectly. By definition, contrast {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AWorldHalfFull"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 A World Half Full}}. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CTPhipps"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 C.T. Phipps}} talks about some of the appeal to the concept here. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sfsignal.com/archives/2015/07/the-appeal-of-grimdark-by-c-t-phipps-author-of-esoterrorism/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 The Appeal of Grimdark.}}}